Problem Summary :- 
                    We have infinitely many boxes numbered 1, 2, 3, ..., all initially white.
                    Chef places two magic mirrors at positions X₁ and X₂ such that:
                    1 ≤ X₁ < X₂
                    He performs the following operation multiple times:
                    Choose a non-negative integer d such that:
                    0 ≤ d < X₁
                    Box X₁ − d is white
                    Color box X₁ − d black
                    The mirror magic automatically colors box X₂ + d black
                    Thus every painting creates a pair of black boxes that satisfy:
                    (X₁ − d) + (X₂ + d) = X₁ + X₂  → constant
                    You are given N black boxes, sorted strictly increasing.
                    Determine whether they can be produced by such mirrored pair operations.


Key Insight (Core Logic) :- 
                            For the configuration to be possible:
                            For every pair of symmetric positions,
                            their sum must be constant, equal to:
                            A[0] + A[N−1]
                            So we only need to check:
                            A[i] + A[N−1−i] == A[0] + A[N−1]   for all i in 0 … (N/2 - 1)
                            If all pairs satisfy this equality → the configuration is valid.

Approach ;- 
              Read N and the array A[]
              Compute target = A[0] + A[N−1]
              Check all symmetric pairs:
              If any pair sum differs from target → impossible
              Output "Yes" or "No"


Time & Space Complexity :- 
                            Aspect	Complexity
                            Time	O(N) per test case
                            Space	O(1) (ignoring input array)


Sample Check :-
                  For black boxes:
                  A = [3, 7, 9, 13]
                  Pairs:
                  3 + 13 = 16
                  7 + 9 = 16
                  All sums match → Possible.

Java Implementation (Cleaned & Commented) :-
                                              import java.util.*;
                                              
                                              class Codechef {
                                                  public static void main(String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception {
                                                      Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
                                                      
                                                      int T = sc.nextInt();
                                                      while (T-- > 0) {
                                                          
                                                          int N = sc.nextInt();
                                                          int[] A = new int[N];
                                                          
                                                          for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
                                                              A[i] = sc.nextInt();
                                                          }
                                              
                                                          boolean ok = true;
                                              
                                                          // Expected sum of symmetric positions
                                                          int target = A[0] + A[N - 1];
                                              
                                                          // Check pairwise symmetric sums
                                                          for (int i = 0; i < N / 2; i++) {
                                                              if (A[i] + A[N - 1 - i] != target) {
                                                                  ok = false;
                                                                  break;
                                                              }
                                                          }
                                              
                                                          System.out.println(ok ? "Yes" : "No");
                                                      }

        sc.close();
    }
}
